      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/46/929",
      "text": [
        ": «إِذَا سَجَدَ أَحَدُكُمْ فَلْيُبَاشِرْ بِكَفَّيْهِ اَلْأَرْضَ لَعَلَّ اَللَّهَ يَدْفَعُ عَنْهُ اَلْغُلَّ يَوْمَ اَلْقِيَامَةِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.929 - Ismail ibn Muslim narrated from Imam Al-Sadiq, from his father (as), who said:\n\"When any of you performs Sujood (prostration), let them place their palms directly on the ground, so that Allah (swt) may protect them from shackles on the Day of Judgment.\""
        ]
      }
